description: Metallica Metals Corp. operates as a junior exploration company that explores for gold, silver, platinum, and palladium properties. Its flagship asset is the Starr project located in the Shebandowan Greenstone Belt, Ontario. It also holds 100% interest in the Richview Pine Project and the Sammy RidgeLine Project located in Northwestern Ontario. The company was formerly known as Cameo Industries Corp. and changed its name to Metallica Metals Corp. in December 2020. Metallica Metals Corp. was incorporated in 1987 and is based in Vancouver, Canada.
ceo: Mr. Benoit  Desormeaux C.A., CPA, CA, CPA
